  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/817",
  "title": "new searchBox option: queryHook",
  "body": "``` js\nsearchBox({\n  // called everytime we would do a search request\n  queryHook: function(inputValue, search) {\n    return true; // do the search request\n    // return false; // don't do the search request\n    // search(); // you can call this to do the search with the provided query that would have done a search request\n  }\n});\n```\n\nThis will solve #776.\n\n@hkdobrev I am not sure to get the use case of being able to replace the query when calling search() as you proposed in https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/776#issuecomment-173373658.\n\nCan you tell us more about the use case? I am not talking about https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/4#issuecomment-173337033\n",
